<sect1>Using the keyboard<p>

I tried to optimize the work flow for the use with the keyboard.
So all of the functions are reachable this way.

<descrip>
  <label id="smart-search">
  <tag/TAB/
    The cursor is moved to the smart search input field.
    If you start typing an expression in this field, <tt/kvoctrain/
    will search the next best match after each key. The cursor
    in the vocabulary is then moved to this location.

    If you press <tt/Return/ it will move to the next match.

    If you additionally keep SHIFT pressed while entering the next
    letter of your word (or press <tt/Return/ for the next match)
    only entries that match from the <bf/beginning/ of the expressions are
    recognized.
    
    Pressing SHIFT-tab will move back to the vocabulary.
    
  <tag/SPACE/
    There are two possibilities:

    <itemize>
     <item>
      <tt/SPACE/ for its own selects or de-selects the current row.
      This means this
      line is included in (or excluded from) the next query. When selected,
      the row appears in a bold face font.
      
     <item>
      If you press a shift key (one of shift, control or alt) together
      with the <tt/SPACE/ key, the current entry is assigned the lesson which
      is shown in the lessons listbox in the toolbar. If the entry was already
      assigned a lesson, it will belong to no lesson afterwards.
    </itemize>
  
  <tag/Cursor LEFT/
    The cursor in the vocabulary is moved one column to the left.
    If it has reached the leftmost column, nothing happens.

  <tag/Cursor RIGHT/
    The cursor in the vocabulary is moved one column to the right.
    If it has reached the rightmost column, nothing happens.

  <tag/Cursor UP/
    The cursor in the vocabulary is moved one row upwards.
    If it has reached the topmost row, nothing happens.

  <tag/Cursor DOWN/
    The cursor in the vocabulary is moved one row downwards.
    If it has reached the bottommost row, nothing happens.

  <tag/Cursor PAGE UP/
    The cursor in the vocabulary is moved one page (the amount of
    visible lines -1) upwards.
    If the cursor would exceed the first possible row, nothing happens.

  <tag/Cursor PAGE DOWN/
    The cursor in the vocabulary is moved one page downwards.
    If the cursor would exceed the last possible row, nothing happens.

  <tag/ENTER/
    <label id="key-enter">
    Invoke dialog for modification of this entry.

  <tag/INS/
    <label id="key-insert">
    Invokes a dialog to enter a new original expression and
    appends a new row with this expression at the end of the
    vocabulary. The cursor is moved to the end of the vocabulary
    afterwards.
    <p>
    If you have selected smart appending you are prompted to
    enter originals and their translations until you stop by
    pressing the ESC key.
    
  <tag/DEL/
    <label id="key-delete">
    After confirmation of a safety dialog, the currently selected
    row or selection is removed from the vocabulary.

  <tag/+ -/
    Pressing the control key and one of the two number pad keys, + or -, you can
    choose the previous or next item in the combo box determinig the current
    lesson. If you don't have a number pad ypu may also use the normal + or - keys.

</descrip>

Some of the menus also have accelerator keys. They are shown on the
according entry on the right side.

The buttons on top of the rows are acessible by the keyboard. To avoid
clashes with the shortcuts for the main menu you have to press SHIFT + ALT
and the key of underlined letter in the button text.
Then the corresponding <htmlurl url="#header-menu"  name="header menu">
will pop up.

<p>&nbsp;<p>

<sect1>Using the mouse<p>
<itemize>
  <item>
    Double clicking an expression in the table will invoke the
    <htmlurl url="#entry-dlg"  name="dialog"> to modify this entry.
    
  <item>
    Left mouse click in of the header buttons will sort this column in ascending
    order. The next click will sort in descending order.
  <item>
    Keeping pressed the left mouse button for about 1 second in on of the table
    header buttons will pop up its
    <htmlurl url="#header-menu"  name="header menu">.
</itemize>

<p>&nbsp;<p>

<sect1>Working on multiple selections<p>

It is possible to mark arbitrary ranges. You can then
modify one or more properties for the selection or save them as a new file.

<itemize>
 <item>
  If you keep the control key pressed while clicking on an entry, the whole row is
  marked for further processing. A click on a marked entry will remove this type
  of selection.

 <item>
  When you additionally press a shift key when clicking on an entry, the
  selection will be extended (or shrunk if you additionally press the control key)
  from the current entry to the point where the cursor was previously.
</itemize>

The selection will disappear after a simple mouse click in a table cell
without a key pressed.

It is also possible to create multiple selections with the cursor keys.
The shift and control keys have the same function here. If you want to
move the cursor to an other area you have to keep the alt key depressed 
to prevent the selection from disappearing. If you want to select several
areas you will have to press a lot of keys, but it works.

If you invoke the edit dialog to modify a selection the dialog
appears differently. Some properties are disabled. For example it does
not make sense to edit the expression itself or the remark of a
whole range.

All selectable fields are empty at the beginning to represent the
unmodified state. Once you have modified a property
there will be contents in it's field and only those properties
are altered in your selection.

