Here you just enter the the comparison forms of the adjective.

<p>
   &nbsp;
<p>

<sect1>Properties from or to the original<p>

For some properties it is possible to set up values <bf/from/ the
original or <bf/to/ the original. For example you can have a grade
when querying the translation (=> from). The opposite is the grade
when querying the original when one of the translations is given(=> to).

  <figure>
    <eps file="entry5-dlg.eps">
    <IMG
     BORDER="0"
     WIDTH="624"
     HEIGHT="512"
     SRC="entry5-dlg.png"
     ALT="[from/to entry dialog]">
  </figure>

<descrip>
  <tag/Grade/
    Contains the current grade of this expression.

  <tag/False friend/
    Sometimes there is a word in a foreign language that looks like a word in
    your native language so you think it must have the same meaning. But in fact,
    it is not.
    
    Enter such words in this field.

  <tag/Last query date/
    This is the date when this entry was last queried.
    If it was never queried yet you only see "--".

    For convinience reasons there are two buttons to 
    set the current date or reset to "never queried".

    Due to internal reasons, it is not possible to store dates
    before Aug. 12 1999 with every version of <tt/kvoctrain/!
    
  <tag/Query count/
    Designates how often this entry was queried.

  <tag/Bad count/
    Shows the amount of times you did not know the right answer.

</descrip>



<sect>Query dialogs<p>

<label id="query-dlg">

<sect1>Normal random query<p>

After selecting "Create random query" from the
<htmlurl url="#header-menu" name="header menu"> the vocabulary disappers.

Then all entries that match your current
<htmlurl url="#options6-dlg" name="threshholds">.
are put into a
list and shown in random order with the following dialog box.

  <figure>
    <eps file="query-dlg.eps">
    <IMG
     BORDER="0"
     WIDTH="608"
     HEIGHT="436"
     SRC="query-dlg.png"
     ALT="[random query dialog]">
  </figure>

 In the area with the original expression there are some properties
 you can enable  pageto give you some hints.
 
<descrip>
 <tag/Edit/
   If you find a mistake with a query you can invoke the edit dialog
   immediately and correct it.
   
 <tag/Show more/
   Each click on this button will show one more character of the solution
   to give you a little help.
   
 <tag/Show all/
   Shows the complete solution in the "Translation" field.
   
 <tag/Verify/
   Not implemented yet. Later version will take the content in the field
   translation and determine using a more or less smart algorithm if the
   answer was correct.
   
 <tag/Don`t know/
   Tells <tt/kvoctrain/ that you did not know the answer and that
   the according grade must be lowered.

 <tag/Know it/
   Click this button to tell <tt/kvoctrain/ that you knew the answer
   correctly. This entry is then removed from the "bad list".
   
 <tag/Stop query/
   Stop query mode and show vocabulary again.
   
 <tag/Options/
   Invoke <htmlurl url="#options-dlg"  name="options dialog">.
   
</descrip>

In the right top corner you see two progress display that indicate the
remaining time and the amount of queries to come.

The query of the current lesson is repeated until all its expressions
are known.
The amount of retries of the current lesson is shown below the progress indicator.

<p>&nbsp;<p>

I regret to admit, but usually I don`t know the solution :-(. For that reason
the <tt/Return/ key has special behaviour, which I found convenient:


<itemize>
 <item>
   First pressing <tt/Return/ shows the complete solution (at the beginning
   the button <tt/"Show more"/ is the default button) and makes <tt/"Don`t know"/
   the default button.
 <item>
   Pressing <tt/Return/ the second time will leave
   this dialog and tell <tt/kvoctrain/ you did not know the answer.
</itemize>

At the moment you must decide for your own, if you knew the answer or failed.
Later versions may provide a more or less smart algorithm to make this
decision from a string you entered.

If you knew the corrent answer, the grade is increase by one step. If you did
not know it, the grade is reset to level 1.

